        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I hunted them from about 55th, without my epic.</P><P>I used the fear-kite technique. Set your pet on guard away from the Sun Rev castle near the edge of the plateau (I used the 49th Pet up until 56th, then the monk one from then until EoT).</P><P>Then pull a Sun Rev with Dooming Darkness, pull him to your pet. Then Fear with Dread of Night and set pet on to him. When he is feared I used Cessation of Cor (Sun Revs seem to resist Poison and Magic quite alot and had a better resist rate with Disease, but before then i used Splurt). </P><P>Only thing you have to make sure of is that you keep the sun rev feared and darknessed, and that your pet is buffed.</P><P>Also on a defensive note keep DMF up, and if you get in trouble run off the top of the plateau as the Sun Revs will not follow.</P><P>Hope this helps.</P><P>Drakkonus Venomvein<BR>60th Iksar Warlock<BR>Proud member of United Kingdoms on AB</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

