         I tried reavers in Scarlet Desert a couple of nights ago, when Katta was so full with guard-killing people that they leaked out of the zone-in..hate that. </P><P>Fun experience, I used to hunt the reavers and revenants on the plateau from time to time...but I wont do it again, ever.<BR>Pull reaver with darkness...resist. Run to pet..darkness..resist. Pet gets beat up...resist...in the end I got 6 resists on darkness and my pet died.../feign.</P><P>On one of the next pulls the fear breaks when a reaver is at 24% health...I re-cast fear....resist...resist..resist...resist...at this point the reaver gates back and brings his friends. /feign</P><P>Not sure if its just bad luck, but reavers resists everything now when I try them. (revenants are still easy and rarley resist btw)<BR>Katta on the other hands...full duration for every spell...not a single resist ever...and boring as hell of course. :)</P><P><BR>"The dead aren`t so bad, once ye get to know them."<BR>- Liwjatan the Lich</P><P>Edited by - Liwjatan on 09/30/2002  16:39:38<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
