        <td bgcolor="black" colspan="2"  valign="top">
		<a name="78665"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;10/01/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 08:10:08</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=3369"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=3369')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=78665&amp;TOPIC_ID=7773&amp;FORUM_ID=3&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&amp;Topic_Title=The+Grey+and+killing+LvL+55+reverants&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         It's one of my favourite spots in The Grey. </P><P>At first I tried root/dot. It works just fine, but it's too slow, they have lots of HP. I found that a combination of root/dot and aggro kite works best. I am doing now the following:</P><P>- Run around the lake, all over the rocks, INVIS, to trigger traps. They are annoying.<BR>- Pop pet, park pet at wall, augment it, pet taunt off. <BR>- Run to a sun rev, pull with epic/snare<BR>- root with a low duration root (I preffer Immobilize). Then Splurt/Pyro/Undead slow<BR>- Optionnaly I reapply epic, to have a fresh snare<BR>- send pet . By now the root is alomost finish. Pet will most likely break it anyway with his procs</P><P>Now the Sun rev is REALLY pissed at you and wont turn on pet no matter what. Just kite him around. Resnare when needed. I even have time to run ahead and reapply the 9 sec casting Epic (nice 70% or so snare on epic). I am non stop in Arhc Lich and by the time the skel is dead, I am very close to full mana. They do not summon.  They are always level 54 or 55. Immune to fear (dont get the immune message, but never landed one single fear on them, too high a level for that). I slow them just for security, they dont really hit me or the pet. Like was said, with 100% in AA I get 2% per kill. When I duo with my wife's toon (60 wizard, maxed FT, KEI etc) I get 1% per kill but killing time is more than halved. </P><P>Speaking of wizards and their mana regen. My wife's 15 (FT) + 3 (Metal Clarity) + 3 (epic) + 6 (pet) + 14 (KEI) = 41 Mana per tick. Which kinda blows my 35 (AL) + 1 (earring of solstice) = 36 Mana per tick. True, I dont have Ft items, but still .. they can get sick mana regen, without the HP loss. Oh well :)</P><P><center><img src="http://home.t-online.de/home/iranicus/images/iranicus_lotj.jpg"><br><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12328" target="_new">My Gear</a><BR></center><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

