		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=4400"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=4400')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=78685&amp;TOPIC_ID=7773&amp;FORUM_ID=3&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&amp;Topic_Title=The+Grey+and+killing+LvL+55+reverants&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         you're lvl 60, you've got no fears, here is the most fun way to kill the sun revs in the grey</P><P>1st hard part: go to the Undying Iksars camp, try to pull only one. they're all linked, enjoy</P><P>charm the iksar, bring it to the rev camp (corner), aug it, pull, root the rev and send pet</P><P>go FAR from the pet (casting range limit) so you can cast ST when charm breaks: undying quad for 160+, hit really hard<BR>sun revs are no match for them, the iksar ends the fight against a slowed rev at 90-95%hps, it will be at full hps when you'll have pulled next mob (yup, their regen blows too)</P><P>usually, if you're at about half casting range you'll loose 1 to 2khps before you can land ST</P><P>and that's w/o weapons, cause to make things even funnier you can give your new killer some weapons like Gnoll Hide Lariats (chain procs, don't get hit or you'll never channel again :D), root sword, ..., cause when you'll kill the pet you'll get the weapons back</P><P>of course you need some guts to do this, had a friend doing this with me (i had a stalking, since i'm only lvl 55, was 54 atm), one time we decided to make both pets fight (both augmented), the iksar ate the shissar in like 10 seconds....</P><P><A HREF="http://brunching.com/toys/cyborger.html"><IMG SRC="http://www.brunching.com/cybimages/M/cyb-MASKLINN.gif" WIDTH=240 HEIGHT=150 ALT="Mechanical Artificial Soldier Keen on Logical Infiltration and Nocturnal Nullification" BORDER=0></A><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
