        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=78790&amp;TOPIC_ID=7773&amp;FORUM_ID=3&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&amp;Topic_Title=The+Grey+and+killing+LvL+55+reverants&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Grey is one of my hunting spots I tell almost no one about =p</P><P>The Shissar's there make grey pets as well.  Aug'ed, they eat things alive.  I charmed one, auged it and sent it after the named Revenant at the temple (I splurted and darked the Rev, no fear as I had ST in that spot).  Won with 10% left on pet snakey, I CoS'ed and then killed my pet.  With a Shissar, can kill most of the things there...</P><P>Anyway, the revs, these guys are wimps.  HUGE WIMPS.  I solo them at 59th.  Not fear kiting, straight up melee.  Shackle of spirit, FD to lose slow agro, Vex mob, Shadowbond pet, sit.  Snare at 40%.  20% mana lost on the whole fight.  You will have to repeat the Vex/Bond series a few times, but Spec eats them up.</P><P><i><b><font color=gold><font size=4>Dinomight Questaholic</b></font id=size4><BR>Master of the Lizard Dance on Test  {The Grove}</i></font id=gold><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

